   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv('TruthTableXOR.csv')[['IN1','IN2','OUT1','OUT2']]\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Extending class torchvision.Dataset to make custom data-iterator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class myData(Dataset):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self,df):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.X = [Variable(s) for s in torch.FloatTensor(df[['IN1','IN2']].values)]\n",
    "        self.y = [Variable(s) for s in torch.FloatTensor(df[['OUT1','OUT2']].values)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __getitem__(self,i):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return self.X[i],self.y[i]\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\n",
    "        return len(self.X)                   "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Instance of the class"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "myDataObject = myData(df)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading the object and making torchvision dataset object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Data_loader = torch.utils.data.DataLoader(dataset = myDataObject, batch_size = 1, shuffle = False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining Neural Network"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class XORnet(nn.Module):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        super(XORnet,self).__init__()\n",
    "            \n",
    "        self.linear1 = nn.Linear(in_features = 2, out_features = 3, bias = True)\n",
    "        self.linear2 = nn.Linear(in_features = 3, out_features = 2, bias = True)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def forward(self,t):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        t = self.linear1(t)\n",
    "        t = F.relu(t)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        t = self.linear2(t)\n",
    "        t = F.sigmoid(t)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return t"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Making an XORnet object"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "XORnet(\n",
       "  (linear1): Linear(in_features=2, out_features=3, bias=True)\n",
       "  (linear2): Linear(in_features=3, out_features=2, bias=True)\n",
       ")"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "myNet = XORnet()\n",
    "myNet"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining Loss Function and Optimizer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(myNet.parameters(), lr=0.001,weight_decay=0.0001)\n",
    "criterion = nn.MSELoss()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Defining Training Function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def train(n_epochs):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(n_epochs):\n",
    "        \n",
    "        eloss = 0 \n",
    "        \n",
    "        for u,(a1,a2)in enumerate(Data_loader):\n",
    "\n",
    "            print(u,a1,a2)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            optimizer.zero_grad()   # zero the gradient buffers\n",
    "            \n",
    "            output = myNet(a1)\n",
    "            loss = criterion(output, a2)\n",
    "            eloss+=loss\n",
    "            losses.append(loss)\n",
    "            loss.backward()\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\n",
    "            \n",
    "        print('Epoch: ',i, 'Loss', eloss/4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
